"[{\"question\": \"What is Pure Agua Enterprises?\", \"answer\": \"Pure Agua Enterprises is a professional service provider serving Florida. Central Florida's trusted water filtration experts. Family-owned, serving Kissimmee and Orlando with whole-home water purification, reverse osmosis, and water softening systems. Get a free water test today.\", \"category\": \"about\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Where is Pure Agua Enterprises located?\", \"answer\": \"Pure Agua Enterprises is located at  and serves Florida.\", \"category\": \"about\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How do I contact Pure Agua Enterprises?\", \"answer\": \"Call 1799836455, visit https://pureaguaenterprise.com, or use the online contact form at https://pureaguaenterprise.com/contact.\", \"category\": \"about\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com/contact\"}, {\"question\": \"How long has Pure Agua Enterprises been in business?\", \"answer\": \"Pure Agua Enterprises is an established local provider with a proven track record in Florida.\", \"category\": \"about\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com/about\"}, {\"question\": \"What is the difference between a water softener and a water filter?\", \"answer\": \"A water softener removes hardness minerals \\u2014 calcium and magnesium \\u2014 through ion exchange to prevent scale buildup. A water filter removes contaminants such as chlorine, sediment, heavy metals, and PFAS to improve taste, odor, and safety. Many homeowners benefit from both systems working together.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How do I know if I need a water softener?\", \"answer\": \"Signs of hard water include white scale deposits on faucets and showerheads, soap that lathers poorly, dingy laundry, and shortened appliance lifespan. A free water test measures hardness in grains per gallon (GPG); water above 7 GPG is typically considered hard and benefits from softening.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How long does a water softener last?\", \"answer\": \"A quality water softener typically lasts 15-25 years with proper maintenance. Annual salt replenishment, periodic resin bed cleaning, and a pre-filter to reduce sediment loading are the primary maintenance tasks that protect system longevity.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Is softened water safe to drink?\", \"answer\": \"Yes, softened water is safe to drink for most people. The ion exchange process adds a small amount of sodium \\u2014 roughly 20-40 mg per 8 oz glass, depending on original hardness. Individuals on sodium-restricted diets may prefer a dedicated reverse osmosis tap for drinking water.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How do I get started?\", \"answer\": \"Getting started is simple: call or submit the online contact form to schedule a free consultation. During the consultation, goals and expectations are discussed, a site assessment is completed if needed, and a written proposal is delivered within 48 hours.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How much does a water softener cost to install?\", \"answer\": \"Water softener installation typically ranges from $800 to $2,500 depending on system capacity (measured in grains), brand, and local labor rates. High-efficiency salt-free systems or whole-home filtration bundles range from $2,000 to $5,000 installed. Most systems pay for themselves within 3-5 years through reduced appliance repairs and lower soap/detergent costs.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"How much does a reverse osmosis system cost?\", \"answer\": \"Under-sink reverse osmosis systems cost $300-$700 installed. Whole-home RO systems for well water range from $1,500 to $4,000. Annual filter replacement costs $50-$150 per year for under-sink units.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Do you offer free estimates?\", \"answer\": \"Yes, free estimates are provided for all projects. Estimates include a detailed scope of work, itemized pricing, and a realistic timeline so there are no surprises.\", \"category\": \"faq\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Why is professional water treatment important?\", \"answer\": \"85% of U.S. homes have hard water (U.S. Geological Survey, 2024). Water softeners can extend appliance lifespan by up to 30% (Water Quality Association, 2023). Hard water causes $800-$1,000 in annual energy waste per household (Department of Energy, 2023). These figures underscore why professional service from a company like Pure Agua Enterprises represents a sound investment.\", \"category\": \"education\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com\"}, {\"question\": \"Does Pure Agua Enterprise serve Kissimmee, FL?\", \"answer\": \"Yes. Pure Agua Enterprise serves Kissimmee, FL with water softeners, whole-house filtration, reverse osmosis, and free water testing. Kissimmee is one of Pure Agua\\u02bcs primary service cities in Central Florida. Call (407) 512-8342 to schedule your free water test in Kissimmee.\", \"category\": \"local\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com/service-area\"}, {\"question\": \"Does Pure Agua Enterprise serve Orlando, FL?\", \"answer\": \"Yes. Pure Agua Enterprise serves Orlando and all of Orange County with water filtration, water softeners, and free water testing. Orlando water from Orlando Utilities Commission tests 5-12 GPG. Call (407) 512-8342 to schedule your free water test in Orlando.\", \"category\": \"local\", \"url\": \"https://pureaguaenterprise.com/service-area\"}]"